Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Peel @Garlic{1%clove} and place in the center of a small piece of #foil{}; drizzle with @Olive Oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cinch into a packet. Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Mince @Chives{1/4%ounce}.

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, @Italian Seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper. Place garlic foil packet on same baking sheet.

Roast on top rack until zucchini is browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place tomatoes in a #medium bowl{}; toss with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, @Italian Seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), salt, and pepper. (You'll use the rest of the Italian Seasoning later.) Set aside to marinate.

Once zucchini is tender, transfer to bowl with tomatoes; toss to combine.

Leaving garlic foil packet on baking sheet, carefully wipe off any excess oil. Place @Flatbreads{2} on same baking sheet. (Divide between 2 sheets for 4 servings.)

Return to top rack until flatbreads are lightly toasted and garlic is softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. (For 4, toast on top and middle racks; swap rack positions halfway through toasting.)

While flatbreads toast, melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Flour{1%tablespoon}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, and remaining Italian Seasoning. Whisk constantly until lightly browned, ~{30%seconds}.

Reduce heat to medium low and whisk in @PHILADELPHIA Cream Cheese{4%tablespoon} and @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4) until melted and combined. Season generously with salt and pepper. Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Once garlic is done, carefully transfer to a #cutting board{} and roughly chop.

Heat broiler to high.

Evenly top flatbreads with sauce, roasted garlic, and veggies. Sprinkle with @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}.

Broil flatbreads until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}. (For 4 servings, broil in batches.)

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Slice flatbreads into pieces; sprinkle with chives and @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Divide between plates and serve.